messages.content: Malachite opens his eyes to find himself in the familiar void of his mindscape. It's vast and echoing, like Polaris', but it's filled with floating motes of light and gargantuan, barely seen shapes as far as the eye can see. It's a comforting sort of unknown, horrifying space, full of things that might be animals and luminous eyes that close when you turn to look at them.

Polaris soon fizzes in, the familiar yet (at least, to him) horrifying feeling somewhere between consciousness and unconsciousness, aware that he was now in a mindspace. He began to panic, snapping his eyes open and sitting up, whipping his head around for answers as to why the *hell he’s here* before—
*Are those eyes?*

He stiffens, feeling something alien in the corner of his mind (well, a different sort of alien.). 
"...Hello?"
He calls out, then pauses, listening. Is this just some more weird shit his brain cooked up for him?

“....”
*Oh. That’s why there’s eyes.*
“Mala,” he called back.
"...Polaris?"
“‘Yeah.”

He scans around, finally spotting him in a cluster of lights.
"Wh- shit, you're still dreaming... sorry, do you want me to wake up?"
He shakes his head, walking towards Malachite. “Nah. It feels.. safer here, I think.”

He hovers over. 
"Safer?"
He nods. “I don’t like my mindscape.”
"...Understandable, but yours has a floor, at least."

“...?”
He tilts his head down, looking at what he *thought* was a floor. He was so caught up in his panic of being in a mindscape that he didn’t realize they aren’t exactly on... solid ground.

He chuckles.
"It's kinda weird at first. Do you want to, uh. Look around?"
“What’s there to look at? The eyes close when I meet them, and there’s shapes.. I think.. but I can barely make them out.”
He doesn’t mean to insult, he’s just genuinely curious.

He shrugs.
"Sometimes there's shit floating around. I don't... look at the big shapes. They're either some sort of monster, or... other stuff."

*Huh?*
“‘Other stuff’?”
"... Like I said, I don't look at that shit."

“Why wouldn’t you want to look at stuff in your own—“
...
“Are you.. *avoiding* part of yourself?”
"...There's just other stuff in here, and it's... cooler."
“That’s bull.”
"Just trust me, neither of us want to see that shit. The lights cluster around anything worth looking at."

“That...”
He looks down at his hands, not sure what to say next.
“..We should look at it.”
"...At what?"
He shrugs. “The stuff you don’t usually look at.”
"That's dumb."
“Not to me.”
"Well it's my dreamscape, so let's follow the eyes."
“Fo— what? Will that lead to the stuff you don’t look at?”

"No, the eyes look at cool shit, and the lights float around it."
He gestures to the growing cloud around them.
"See? They like you."

“If they look at stuff they like...” Polaris looks around, as if trying to figure something out.
“I’ll just go where they’re faced away from.”
"Wh- no?"
He didn’t respond, but in his mind he said *yes.* He went up to the closest eye, walking around and behind it and just.. continuing forward.

"H- wait, stop,"
He follows after him, setting a hand on his shoulder.
He continues forward, not paying attention to the hand. “If you guys are all gonna force me to go through my shit, I’m making you go through yours.”
"My shit isn't actively trying to fuck with me, I want to *keep it that way."*

After hearing this, he turns around, facing Malachite with stern eyes.
“I refused to face my shit for over a million fucking years, and look where that got me.”
Turning back around, he started forward again.
*I’m not letting what happened to me happen to you.*

"I *faced* my shit, I went to therapy."
He's getting uncomfortable.
"I got them to be quiet, don't *fuck* with it."
“Therapy doesn’t just *fix* things, Mala. It doesn’t work like that.”
"Well, it's better than it used to be."
“‘Better’ doesn’t mean ‘good’.”

"It means less bad though. I've-"
He sighs.
"I have enough to worry about. I'll deal with this later."

“*What?*” 
He stops in his tracks, turning around and facing Malachite head on. “What *stuff?* Stuff that shouldn’t have concerned you in the first place?”
"I have a life, and- *other people* have lives, and I want to help out. Plus there's the- the *Revolution*. I have shit to do."

He wanted to yell. He wanted to *scream.* This was hypocritical at worst. 
“Yeah? Well that’s in the waking world. We’re in your mindscape, now. No revolution in here.”

"I don't want to think about it, okay?"
He swallows.
"I finally got it to be quiet in here, at least, and that's fine for now."

“It’s going to bite you in the ass.”
He starts walking again.

"It can bite me later,"
He protests, trailing behind apprehensively. *Maybe when they get there it'll just be nothing, maybe it'll be gone this time.*
"I need to be put together."
“You don’t *need* to be anything.”

"Yes, I *do."*
They're getting close. *Maybe it'll be nothing. Maybe they'll get to a dark place and it'll only be darkness.*

“Says *who.*”
*What is ‘it’?*

"Says me. I can't help anyone if I'm having a breakdown."
He slows, shuddering.
"...I'm not going any further."

“Fine.”
Star Platinum appears, picking up Malachite and taking him with Polaris, who hasn’t slowed down a bit.
*Then I’m carrying you.*

"Hey, stop-"
He tries to wriggle away.
*"Jesus*, Polaris, let *go* of me-"
He ignores him.

*...That there, is that it?* 
"Polaris, I'm not kidding, stop- stop it."
He spots... something? He feels something. He moves towards it.

The shape in the distance slowly comes into focus, something huge and undulating illuminated dimly by the swarm of small, pulsating lights that surround them. A deep, sick feeling washes over him, and he can't manage more than a hoarse attempt at protesting.

"..."
He looks to Malachite, concerned, but then remembers they're in a mindscape. Whatever happens here, as long as he is careful and doesn't fuck up badly, they'll be fine. He continues again.

From what he can gather, the thing looks like a mass of ropes, twisting and wormlike as if it's mimicking Hierophant in some disgusting way. It twists around... something he can't quite make out. He feels cold.
"We *saw* it, let's go,"
He pleads, going limp.

"..."
Star's scarf removes itself from the stand, wrapping around Malachite like a protective blanket.
"Seeing it doesn't fix it."
*It's... It looks.. complex.*
The tendrils (for lack of a better word) seem to shrink from them, coiling around the shape in the middle as if trying to hide it. An eye opens beside them to peer at it.

Polaris pauses his treck, giving Malachite a spare amount of mercy and turning to the eye. Malachite said the eyes looks away from stuff like this.. why is this one looking *towards* it?
He approaches it.
It flickers over to him along with Malachite's gaze, before turning back, again in unison.

"....Hey."
He walks closer towards it, moving between it and the.. *thing* they were approaching before.
It stays fixed on the shape, flicking over to him for another moment.

He waves lightly.
*What..* **are** *you...?*
Reaching a hand forward, he moves to sort of... touch.. it? His hand hovers over the eye, waiting to see it's reaction.
It blinks like it's flinching away, and Malachite mirrors it, grimacing.

"..."
Well, he's already come this far. No hesitating now.
He places a hand on it, slowly and carefully, a delicate touch for such rough hands. "Hello."
The eye shivers and closes with a *snik*, reappearing a few feet away to keep staring. It's not solid, more like a little spot of warmth.

*Maybe that was... hm.*
He turns back towards the big mass of.. tentacle... things. Star puts down Malachite, but still hovers over him, protective, as Polaris heads towards it.
Eyes flick into being, flocking to it intently like crows to carrion. The ropy tendrils shy away from their gaze to reveal twisted metal and a growing trickle of liquid.

"...."
Oh.
*Oh.*
It makes... too much sense. Too much vividly horrible sense. 
He turns back to Malachite, and... Star lifts up his shirt a bit. Polaris needs to see.
His jaw tightens as the real monster is revealed, and he flinches away from Star's touch. *Stop it.*

*Keep going.*
Star lifts it up all the way as Polaris moves closer, kneeling down next to Malachite.
He's trembling, shrinking away and looking down at himself with numb horror. Water gushes out of a wound that *should be gone.*

"Malachite..."
He rushes over, skidding on the ground and taking Malachite into his arms. "You... How long has this been here...?"
He shakes his head. *It shouldn't be here at all, he barely remembers.*

*He doesn't... fuck, yeah, right, human memories and mun memories aren't the same.*
He summons Star again, placing Malachite on him and having him hold the smaller mun, walking up to the... water tower..
*This isn't going to hurt me as much as it hurts him...*
*But it's still gonna hurt.*

His eyes go wide. 
"St- stop- stop it,"
He chokes out, swallowing a sob.
"Stop, I don't want- *stop-"*

Star shushes him, combing a large hand through his hair.
"*I'm sorry. You... gotta* feel *things in order to move through them.*"

"No, no-"
He feels sick to his stomach.
"Don't, please, it's *cold*, I don't want to--"
Polaris swallowed his guilt, moving into the weird.. ball of tentacles. Star continued hugging Malachite, trying to give him as much warmth as a stand could muster.

He's gone still in his arms, staring blankly at the water tower with his fingers digging into Star.
"Please,"
He croaks.
"Don't leave me up there, don't leave me up there, don't--"

*Don't... what...?*
He squints, looking directly into the water tower, to the crash where Ma—... Where *Kakyoin* landed.

*"Jotaro*, it's-- it's freezing, and- and- I'm- don't leave me up there."
He whimpers, holding onto him.

"*Shh.. Sh, I won't, Nori. I'm here. I'm right here, you're okay,*" Star whispered to him, carding his hands through Malachite's hair comfortingly. Polaris got closer, climbing up on top of the tentacles and sort of.. launching himself into the air in front of the water tower.
He sobs brokenly. This *can't be happening,* this can't happen-
Polaris keeps having Star reassure Malachite as Polaris drifts closer. There must be *something* to do here... something that'll help.

The tower is quiet, silent apart from the bubbling water and a faint, rhythmic sound. A heartbeat? ...A clock? Whatever is it, it feels like it's echoing through Kakyoin- through *Malachite's* very bones. He doesn't want to be here. He doesn't want to do it again. *He doesn't want to see it.*

*That.. ticking.... where is it coming from...?*
He searches around, turning his head left and right in search for whatever it is. He needs to stop that sound.
He tries to cover his ears, practically clawing at he sides of the head, but it feels like it's pulsed inside and settled into him. He bites back a whimper.

*Mother of... Think—* THINK. *What could that sound be? What happened on Earth....*
His mind carded through his memories as Jotaro, through the lives where he saw Kakyoin during the fight with Dio. What happened...?
Kakyoin smashed into the water tower and he... What did he—
...Time.
He showed Joseph that Dio could stop time.
*There's a clocktower somewhere.*
He started searching more vigorously, looking all over the spiraling mass.

He shudders- *he can't breathe*. Malachite (is it Malachite...?) Looks down at what's left of his torso, numbly tracing his hand over the mangled mess. What happened next? His thoughts flit to his parents (his parents?), Then to his friends, then- a clock. There should be a clock. Where is it?

Can't see the clock, might as well listen.
"*Malachite.. do you know where the clock is?*"

*Does* he know where the clock is? He's supposed to. He's supposed to *help.* He looks up, staring where it should be, and-
...
...Where is it? *Where is it?*
"*Malachite, look at me,*" Star says, tilting the others head to his eyes. Star lifts his chest, up and down, in a breathing-like motion. "*Match me. Then think.*"

He tries. God, he's *trying*, but-
"I, I- whh-" 
His chest heaves with half breaths sucked into tattered lungs.
"Where- I can't- I don't-"
He shakes his head. *He can't help. He doesn't know, so he can't help.*

"*You* can *help. Slow down, please. You're doing great, but you need to trust me. Just.. slow down..*"
Star continues to 'breath', meeting Malachite's eyes.

"I don't-"
He coughs.
"I can't help- I can't tell you--"

"*Why can't you tell me?*"
Star's voice is gentle, surprising coming out of something so... intimidating. But he's trying.

*He can't pass on the message. He's cold, he's fading away, and he can't even tell him.*
"I don't- don't know, I can't-"
*He can't even do it this time, he can't stay strong.*
"*Dio can stop time..*" Star began. "*You shot at the clock tower. You stopped the ticking once, you've stopped it* millions of times. *You can do it again.*"
"*You showed us the secret of The World. You succeeded. You're safe now.*"

*He wants to do it again, he wants to help, he wants to save everyone, but-*
"Nnn, no-"
*This time he can't do it. This time he's not a hero. He's falling apart and he can't do it; he's just a kid on a water tower.*
"U-useless."
He chokes out miserably.
"*Malachite, after all that we've been through... do words like 'useless' and 'impossible' still have meaning to us?*"
*...Malachite?* He hiccups, trying to push himself together enough to gather a breath. He's *Malachite.*

Star nods.
"*You're Malachite.*"

"...I don't want to be here,"
He whispers, still shaking with the rhythmic noise of the clock.
"P-please, please let me leave,"
Star shakes its head no. "*I'm sorry, but not yet. We need to stop the ticking. Can you tell me where it is?*"

He doesn't want to do it again. *He doesn't want to, but-* He nods hesitantly. He needs to, Polaris needs him to.
"It's- I need to-"
He needs to be on the tower, he realizes. He... 
"The Tower, p-"
He can't bring himself to finish the sentence.

Star looks up at Polaris, who was still searching for the tower, and Polaris looks back— as if they were looking at each other with mutual concern.
"*I understand.*"
Star lifted up Malachite, slowly bringing him to Polaris. Don't want to rush things and risk him panicking.
He shivers, he remembers how cold it was, but... he has to do it, he has to help them. That... will do something, presumably?

"It'll help a lot," Polaris says at Star places Malachite into his arms, disappearing after with a reassuring smile.
*At least.. I'm kinda sure it will.*
He clings to him without quite realizing, pulling him closer. *He has to do this, it'll help.*

Floating over to the water tower, Polaris kisses Malachite's forehead.
"You got this. You've done it so many times before. It's going to suck, but you're strong. Don't forget that."
*He is strong, he shouldn't be this scared. He's done this all before.* He jerks his head yes, scrunching his eyes closed. Get it over with.

"You're allowed to be scared, Mala. But being scared and pushing through it is bravery. And you're the bravest person I know." He spoke softly, assured of himself.
"I'm going to put you down now."
He nods again.
He lowered Malachite down, carefully setting him in the crack of the tower and backing up slowly.
He thought he was ready, but- *oh god.* It's different being here, it's freezing. His eyes snap open, staring blindly at dark water that cascades through him. *He has to do this.*

*You've got this.*
Polaris resists the temptation to hold Malachite's hand— he doesn't want this to mess up.

The tendrils split, revealing a city and hints of starry skies.
Kakyoin Noriaki can't move. He can't breath, he can't speak, but his mind is flying at a mile a minute. He looks up at the sky, numbly wondering if his parents are awake. They don't know he's here, he recalls, they don't know he's half a world away trying to save the only other people he's ever cared about.

Polaris...
He looks down at himself.
No. Jotaro looks around at the starry sky, wondering if any of the burning balls of gas are watching this happen from those light years away.
He looks at Kakyoin. The hole in his torso... Star.. *The World...* is capable of that...
Kakyoin is about to reveal what else they're capable of, huh?

He shakes away thoughts of his parents, forcing himself to look up. Hierophant Green, his closest companion, is draped over the city like a delicate web, tattered threads glinting brightly with the streetlights below. 
...Why didn't DIO set it off? He tore Hierophant to shreds, why couldn't he *feel* it?

It's not just speed, it's more that that- did he teleport? No, that wouldn't break the web... his eyes flit over the cityscape, searching for something, *anything-*
There's a faint ticking... the clock tower.
His eyes widen, he *knows*, but-
He feels his vision start to fade, sight pouring out of him alongside the water. He's running out of time, he realizes as he takes aim at the face of the clock. Might as well try to use what he has left.

It's... done. He did it, and he's still here. Kakyoin (shouldn't he be someone else?) is still here, on this tower, waiting for the rest of his vision to slip away. He wonders, briefly, if anyone will come get him, but- he looks down at what's left of his body with what's left of his vision, and shivers. Even if they did come to him, they couldn't help, and he'd still be bleeding out on a water tower. He turns blurred eyes up to the sky a final time, accepting it. He hopes this helped, even just a little. He hopes this was worth it.
It's cold, he thinks, finally drifting off.

"Kakyoin..." Jotaro whispers from his place on top of the building. "Kakyoin— *KAKYOIN!*"
Star Platinum launches himself up to the other teen, landing on the water tower's platform and jumping to Kakyoin, ripping him off of it carefully.
"Fuck, fuck, *fuck—* I-I need to- we need to get out of here. The Speedwagon Foundation, they'll fix you.. th-they'll..."
He shook his head. "*Come on.*"
He jumps off the water tower and to the ground, outside of the range of... something... what were they.. *where* were they....?

He's shaking, trying to pull in ragged breaths. Someone's here, but he's still so *cold-* 
"Jotaro?"
He rasps, trying to clear the fog from behind his eyes.

"K— Nori— Nori, I'm here.. I'm getting you to the Speedwagon Foundation. They're going to fix you."
He was running— where is he running? This doesn't feel right.

"Jo-"
*No, that's not right.*
"...Polaris?"
He whispers, holding on with all the strength he can muster.

*Polaris.. That's my name. That's my name..?*
He slowed down to a halt, his vision of himself and.. whoever he was holding... fizzling in and out of something else.
"...Mala. We did it. *You did it.*"
He's silent, still shivering, and trying to pull Polaris closer.
"We're safe. We're *all* safe. The clocktower stopped ticking."
He still doesn't reply, just trying to press his face into Polaris. A sob bubbles out of him.
He lets himself fall onto his behind, allowing Malachite to sit on his lap and just.. cry.

He claws at Polaris' shirt, shoulders heaving as he cries into his shoulder. It was quiet for so long, *he ignored it for so long-*
"Wh-why?"
He gasps, still trying to find his breath.
"I had to.." he mumbles, carefully combing a hand through Malachite's hair, holding onto him snuggly.

"I d- I didn't *w-want* to-"
He's barely coherent, spitting out words between tears.

"It had to happen. Now, or later.."
He's trying *so hard* to be comforting.. he just hopes it's working. Seeing Malachite so.. so *broken down* is.. different from what he's used to. He hope he never has to see it again. Though, if he has to....
*I swear, I'll always be there for you.*
He kisses Malachite's temple.

*"Why* did it h- have to happen?"
He hates it, he hates the memory, he hates thinking about tattered green ribbons and water so icy it burns.

*He...*
"You have to.. *think* of stuff to move passed it."
*How the hell am I supposed to explain this...?*
"Remember our arguments? Where we argued over if Morise was a good parent to me or not?"
He bobs his head.

"You.."
Hm.
"You *made* me think about it. And I still am. Maybe I'll never stop. But at least it's better than before. I got the hardest part over with..." *I think.*

"I- I *know* it's bad,"
He raises his voice without realizing.
"I kn- know it's bad, that's, that's why I *stopped thinking about it."*
"You can't just *stop* thinking about it."
"I was so- so- so *scared,* it-"

"We both were.."
He keeps combing his hand through his hair, pushing himself into a more comfortable sitting position.
"But.. You're glad that it's over... right?"

"I *know* it's over, that- that doesn't-"
It doesn't matter that it's over, it's not a reasonable fear; he knows it's in the past, knowing that doesn't dampen the pang of revulsion when he sees his scar. It doesn't make the senseless terror any better.

"Malachite..."
Polaris carefully cups his chin, tilting it up to meet his gaze.
"You know we don't blame you for being afraid, right?"

**"It's not *about* that-"**
Malachite looks like a mess; he's frustrated, and tired, and tearstained, and still trying to shake the chill from his bones.
"I'm still- I'm still afraid, it's still *horrible,"*

"..."
He wants to let Malachite speak.

"I- I know you would help, but it wouldn't- *do* anything, I still look like- *this*," 
He reaches a hand down, laying it over his abdomen.
"...and I still- still remember how cold it was, and how there was n- nobody there, and-"

"... "
Saying sorry for not being there would be useless, at this point. So instead, Polaris gently takes Malachite's hand in his, hold it up to his vertical scar.
"I look like this. You still love me anyway."

"I'm n-not worried about that,"
He mumbles, curling farther in on himself.
"It's not about- how it looks, it's about- it's a *reminder."*

"...I can't.. take away the trauma. I can't take away the pain."
*In fact, doing this might've caused you more pain...*
"But I can.."
*What can I do..?*
"I can.. help you move passed it. Without throwing it away."
He mumbles incomprehensibly, feeling dizzy.

*Maybe he's waking up...*
He doesn't continue speaking, instead deciding to.. rock back and forth, combing his hair through Malachite's hair again and singing softly to him.
He feels... calmer, slightly. It's nice to have someone here with him, at least. Not being alone is... comforting.

*Can I...*
He tries doing what Malachite taught him. Think of what you really want, and....
A soft pillow and thick blanket form, covering Malachite and giving him something to rest on.
*You'll feel better when we're awake..* he thinks to himself, kissing Malachite's cheek. *I promise.*

He hiccups quietly, clinging to Polaris.
 *"Don't leave."*
He mumbles.

"I won't.."
*I'm never leaving your side.*
*I promise.*

Malachite awakes in his mindscape with a start, still panting and clawing as he comes to his senses. He's still riding an adrenaline high, and what he did to Polaris hasn't quite sunken in yet. *Speaking of Polaris...* something in here is out of place. There's an intruder at the corner of his mind.
Polaris was sitting down a while away, just.. staring forward. His neck had marks in it and his scars were noticibly bigger, glowing brightly.

His heart tries to clamber out of his throat as he sees him, his gut twisting with conflicting emotions (and something else...?). He doesn't know how to approach, so he sits down as well, waiting for... something. Anything.

He twists around, having heard the shuffling, looking at Malachite with tired, angry eyes for a moment, before turning back around, not caring for him and instead choosing to just.. look at the weird eyes.
The eyes stare back with a sort of sadness behind their cold, glistening detachment. Malachite sighs and flops onto the ground, temper cooled very slightly by the peaceful space.
Polaris just.. sighs, holding a hand up to the eye. Last time, that one eye shied away.. maybe this time..?

It shivers as he reaches toward it, blinking and flinching as if it's scared, but after a moment it bumps into his hand for a split second. An image flashes into his head, so quick he can't quite make it out.
He holds in a gasp, not having expected that, but trying to keep himself still. These.. *eyes* are part of Malachite's mindscape. If they don't trust him, then..
The eye stops and stares directly at him, quivering slightly and emitting a faint hum.

"..?"
He reaches forward again, slow and hesitant. He's.. not entirely sure what he's doing.
This time it doesn't flinch back as much, and his hand is enveloped in a strange, quasi-organic heat as his vision flickers and fades.

*...Huh.*
He continues forward, placing his hand on the eye gently, letting his eyes flutter shut. Not like he can fuckin' see, anyways.
The world around him warps like the air on a hot day, and he finds himself staring into the same void from a different angle. Several feet away, Malachite shudders and sits up, blinking.

Polaris.. tries to blink. He's not sure if he can, but he definitely tries.
*What the hell...?*
Malachite tries to blink this weird feeling out of his eyes. Polaris' vision flickers, panning from side to side like it's looking for something.

Polaris shivers. It almost feels like when he's looking through Star Platinum's eyes, instead of.. his own...
*Am I.. seeing through Malachite's eyes..?*

The image projected onto his eyelids jerks to the side, and he's met with the sight of himself, hand resting on the luminous eye.
Malachite stares at him, slightly confused.

Polaris turns his own head around at Malachite and sees his own head turn around to look at him.
"...Huh."
*What the fuck?* He stands, swaying slightly as he gets to his feet.

He stays quiet, watching as his own vision follows Malachite's.
*...This feels weird.*
"...What?"

"Uh."
*Am I supposed to say something? Can he hear me??*

"What are you..."
He steps forward, slightly wobbly from their... activities in the waking world. His neck hurts.

*Oh fuck—*
He twists his body, slipping and falling onto the ground. Why is he shaking..?

He snaps out of his sleepy state and runs up to Polaris, kneeling beside him.
"Shit, are you alright?"
"Fuck off— get *away—*" he stutters, moving back further.

He flinches back.
"Polaris? What-"

After a moment, he realizes what he said, and he backs up just a bit further, swallowing.
His scars hurt, being noticably bigger than before, and he's shaking... *why* is he fucking *shaking?*

He grimaces, wincing at the scars. *Fuck, did he do that?*
"...I'm sorry,"
He murmurs, standing and stepping back.
He looks down, wide eyed and dilated pupils going bigger and smaller in his panic. "...I.. Don't be sorry."

He swallows. 
"Are you- are you okay?"

He swallows as well, blinking groggily.
"...I don't know."

"...Why are we here?"
He's having some trouble remembering how he got from point A (attempted murder) to point B (gay baby jail).

After swallowing one last time, he gets his grip on the ground, pushing himself up and sitting limply. Even in there, he can barely feel his lower body.
"I.. I think Cerise hypnotized us."

*...That was probably for the best.*
"Ah, yeah... I can't believe I actually-"
He swallows, his mouth dry.

"..."
He stays quiet. Even now, he's still fighting the urge to start it again.

"Did... did I do that?"
He whispers, staring at Polaris' scars. Being pissed isn't top priority right now, it's in the compartment underneath 'check on Polaris.'
"Do.. what?"
"Your scars, they look... painful."
He scoffs. "That's nothing new."

*He brought the attitude into their mindscape, huh?*
"I'm just asking, Polaris, I'm worried."
"What are you talking about?" he asks, furrowing his brow. He's genuinely confused.

"I'm talking about how your scars look like they're splitting you open, Polaris, you look like- like you're falling apart at the seams."
The hostility in the air sets off a dull, droning pain in his head to compliment the rotting ache inside his body.

Polaris swallowed, pupils growing bigger and smaller with each moment. Not like he could fucking *stand up*, so he’s sorta just.. forced to deal with the panic.

Malachite wakes up in his mindscape absolutely *pissed.* The whole thing is strange and muffled, colors and lights bleeding into shifting clouds that form into vague shapes in his peripheral vision. He yells in frustration, listening to the sound echo and distort in the vast darkness.
